Design a plan to refactor the claude-hook-handler tool to use SQLite + Prisma instead of NDJSON file for event logging.

## Current Architecture

The tool is a Node.js/TypeScript CLI at `/Users/stephanostsoucas/gossamer/src/handler.ts`.

### Current event storage (NDJSON)
- Events are appended to a flat NDJSON file (one JSON per line)
- `writeEventLog(eventsPath, input, blocked, state)` appends a record
- `runReconstruct` reads all lines, replays them to rebuild markdown
- EventRecord interface:
  ```typescript
  interface EventRecord {
    timestamp: string;
    event: string;       // hook_event_name
    blocked: boolean;
    data: HookInput;     // full raw hook payload as JSON
    summary?: string;    // AI-generated (only for UserPromptSubmit)
    keywords?: string[]; // AI-generated (only for UserPromptSubmit)
  }
  ```

### Current State (JSON file)
- `State` = `{ sessions, agentParents, pendingToolUses }` stored in `~/.claude/sessions-state.json`
- Read/written on every hook invocation

### Key data interfaces
```typescript
interface SessionRecord {
  sessionId: string;
  startedAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
  cwd: string;
  repoRoot?: string;
  repoName?: string;
  parentSessionId?: string;
  gitUserName?: string;
  gitUserEmail?: string;
  prompt?: string;
  summary?: string;
  keywords?: string[];
}

interface PendingToolUse {
  tool_use_id: string;
  tool_name: string;
  tool_input?: unknown;
  startedAt: string;
}

// State
interface State {
  sessions: Record<string, SessionRecord>;
  agentParents: Record<string, string>;
  pendingToolUses: Record<string, PendingToolUse>;
}
```

